            <p>
                The Household Budgeter is a Web-based software application designed for creating and managing budgets for household finances and the balancing of
                bank accounts. It function as an online service that may be used in multiple households/families throughout the world.
            </p>
            <p>
                The Household Budgeter project is similar in nature to many such commercial-grade products (i.e. AceMoney, BudgetPulse, Moneydance, Pocketsmith,
                QuickBooks, EveryDollar, etc.) with which most employers are familiar.
            </p>
            <p>
                This project has been built as a Web-based service application using the Microsoft Visual Studio 2015 IDE, MVC,
                MS Code-First database schema using Entity Framework with user-level security, and web pages built with
                HTML5, Twitter Bootstrap, and model binding with Razor.
            </p>
